  "content": "<div><br></div>\n<div>Set during Xmas </div>\n<div>Empty Xmas tree in el’s house, she helps sheen set up Xmas lights</div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>Set up el’s motivation</div>\n<div>Reimagines sheen’s death as she meets new people</div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>EL sketches what she thinks Sheen is doing every time she leaves her alone. The camera stays with el. We don’t know what sheen is doing. </div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>El should make some efforts to try and talk through the film so when she finally can it is satisfying. </div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>Does she need to have bullies? Isn’t it kinda kids versus adults? If she does have a bully, her and the bully are more similar than they thought. Bullies mom is an addict too. </div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>Its a story about woman, generations of woman, and the dangers of what might happen to them. El, Sheen, El’s mom, Sandra</div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div><img style=\"max-width: 100%; max-height: 100%;\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,",
